ENERGY
                                                          Develop and use a model of two objects interacting through electric or magnetic fields to illustrate the forces
              Performance Expectation                     between objects and the changes in energy of the objects due to the interaction.
                                                          Physical Science: Examples of models could include drawings, diagrams, simulations and texts, such as what
                                                          happens when two charged objects or two magnetic poles are near each other.
               Clarification Statement
                                                          Physics: Examples of models could include drawings, diagrams, and texts, such as drawings of what happens when
                                                          two charges of opposite polarity are near each other.
