                                                                                                                                                              HS-PS4-1
WAVES AND THEIR APPLICATIONS IN TECHNOLOGIES FOR INFORMATION TRANSFER
                                                            Use mathematical representations to support a claim regarding relationships among the frequency, wavelength,
             Performance Expectation                        and speed of waves traveling in various media.
                                                            Physical Science: Emphasis is on describing waves both qualitatively and quantitatively. Qualitative focus includes
                                                            standard repeating waves and transmission/absorption of electromagnetic waves/radiation.
              Clarification Statement                       Physics: Examples of data could include electromagnetic radiation traveling through a vacuum and glass, sound
                                                            waves traveling through air and water, and seismic waves traveling through the Earth. Emphasis is on algebraic
                                                            relationships and describing those relationships qualitatively.
         Science & Engineering Practices                                   Disciplinary Core Ideas                                    Crosscutting Concepts
1. Asking questions and defining problems                   WAVE PROPERTIES                                             CAUSE AND EFFECT
2. Developing and using models                              The wavelength and frequency of a wave are related to       Empirical evidence is required to differentiate between
                                                            one another by the speed of travel of the wave, which       cause and correlation and make claims about specific
3. Planning and carrying out investigations                 depends on the type of wave and the medium through          causes and effects.
4. Analyzing and interpreting data                          which it is passing. (HS.PS4A.a)
