   Mathematical and computational thinking in 9-12
   builds on K-8 experiences and progresses to using
   algebraic thinking and analysis, a range of linear and
   nonlinear functions (e.g. trigonometric, exponential
   and logarithmic) and computational tools for statistical
   analysis to analyze, represent, and model data. Simple
   computational simulations are created and used based
   on mathematical models of basic assumptions.
 • Use mathematical, computational, and/or algorithmic
