                                                                                                                                                                           PS
                                                                                                                                                               HS-PS1-1
MATTER AND ITS INTERACTIONS
                                                          Use the periodic table as a model to predict the relative properties of elements based on the patterns of electrons
              Performance Expectation                     in the outermost energy level and the composition of the nucleus of atoms.
                                                          Physical Science: Examples of properties that could be predicted from patterns could include metals, nonmetals,
                                                          metalloids, number of valence electrons, types of bonds formed, or atomic mass. Emphasis is on main group elements.
               Clarification Statement                    Chemistry: Examples of properties that could be predicted from patterns could include reactivity of metals, types of
                                                          bonds formed, numbers of bonds formed, atomic radius, atomic mass, or reactions with oxygen. Emphasis is on main
                                                          group elements and qualitative understanding of the relative trends of ionization energy and electronegativity.
