MOTION AND STABILITY: FORCES AND INTERACTIONS
                                                            Plan and conduct an investigation to provide evidence that an electric current can produce a magnetic field and
             Performance Expectation                        that a changing magnetic field can produce an electric current.
                                                            Physical Science: Emphasis is on designing and conducting investigations including evaluating simple series and
                                                            parallel circuits. Qualitative evidence is used to explain the relationship between a current-carrying wire and a
                                                            magnetic compass.
               Clarification Statement                      Physics: Evidence of changes within a circuit can be represented numerically, graphically, or algebraically using
                                                            Ohm’s law. Emphasis is on designing and conducting investigations using qualitative evidence to determine the
                                                            relationship between electric current and magnetic fields. Examples of evidence can include movement of a
                                                            magnetic compass needle when placed in the vicinity of a current-carrying wire, and a magnet passing through a
                                                            coil that turns on the light of a Faraday flashlight.
