ENVIRONMENTAL AWARENESS AND PROTECTION
                                                             Use multiple lines of evidence to construct an argument addressing the negative impacts that introduced
             Performance Expectation                         organisms have on Louisiana’s native species.
                                                             The exotic organisms introduced in Louisiana include plants such as Chinese tallow, kudzu and water hyacynth
                                                             and animals including nutria, Asian tiger mosquitoes and zebra mussels. These organisms can have impacts on
              Clarification Statement                        scales ranging from the level of the individual (e.g. competition) to that of the landscape (e.g. the destruction of
                                                             coastal marshes by nutria).
