EARTH’S SYSTEMS
                                                         Analyze geoscience data to make the claim that one change to Earth’s surface can create feedbacks that cause
            Performance Expectation                      changes to other Earth’s systems.
                                                         Examples could include climate feedbacks such as how an increase in greenhouse gases causes a rise in global
                                                         temperatures that melts glacial ice which reduces the amount of sunlight reflected from Earth’s surface increasing
                                                         surface temperatures and further reducing the amount of ice. Examples could also be taken from other system
             Clarification Statement                     interactions such as how the loss of ground vegetation causes an increase in water runoff and soil erosion; how
                                                         damned rivers increase ground water recharge, decrease sediment transport, and increase coastal erosion; or how
                                                         the loss of wetlands causes a decrease in local humidity that further reduces the wetland extent.
