HISTORY OF EARTH
                                                               Apply scientific reasoning and evidence from ancient Earth materials, meteorites, and other planetary surfaces to
             Performance Expectation                           construct an account of Earth’s formation and early history.
                                                               Emphasis is on using available evidence within the solar system to reconstruct the early history of Earth, which
                                                               formed along with the rest of the solar system 4.6 billion years ago. Examples include the absolute age of ancient
              Clarification Statement                          materials (obtained by radiometric dating of meteorites, moon rocks, and Earth’s oldest materials), the sizes and
                                                               compositions of solar system objects, and the impact cratering record of planetary surfaces.
