                                                                                                                                                                                  ES
                                                                                                                                                                 HS-ESS2-7
EARTH’S SYSTEMS
             Performance Expectation                          Construct an argument based on evidence about the simultaneous coevolution of Earth systems and life on Earth.
                                                              Emphasis is on the dynamic causes, effects, and feedbacks between the biosphere and Earth’s other systems,
                                                              whereby geoscience factors control the evolution of life, which in turn continuously alters Earth’s surface. Examples
                                                              include how photosynthetic life altered the atmosphere through the production of oxygen, which in turn increased
              Clarification Statement                         weathering rates and allowed for the evolution of animal life; how microbial life on land increased the formation of
                                                              soil, which in turn allowed for the evolution of land plants; or how the evolution of corals created reefs that altered
                                                              patterns of erosion and deposition along coastlines and provided habitats for the evolution of new life forms.
         Science & Engineering Practices                                      Disciplinary Core Ideas                                       Crosscutting Concepts
