                                                              other organisms that captured carbon dioxide and                how things change and how they remain stable.
3. Planning and carrying out investigations                   released oxygen. (HS.ESS2D.b)
4. Analyzing and interpreting data
                                                              BIOGEOLOGY
5. Using mathematics and computational thinking               The many dynamic and delicate feedbacks between the
6. Constructing explanations and designing solutions          biosphere and other Earth systems cause a continual
                                                              co-evolution of Earth’s surface and the life that exists on
7. Engaging in argument from evidence: Engaging
                                                              it. (HS.ESS2E.a)
