                                                                                                                                                          HS-PS1-8
MATTER AND ITS INTERACTIONS
                                                          Develop models to illustrate the changes in the composition of the nucleus of the atom and the energy released
              Performance Expectation                     during the processes of fission, fusion, and radioactive decay.
                                                          Physical Science: Emphasis is only on simple qualitative models, such as pictures or diagrams, and on the scale
                                                          of energy released in nuclear processes relative to other kinds of transformations. Radioactive decay focus is on
                                                          its relationship to half-life.
               Clarification Statement
                                                          Chemistry: Emphasis is on simple qualitative models, such as pictures or diagrams, and on the scale of energy
                                                          released in nuclear processes relative to other kinds of transformations. Emphasis is on alpha, beta, and gamma
                                                          radioactive decays.
