                                                                                                                                                              HS-PS3-1
ENERGY
                                                          Create a computational model to calculate the change in the energy of one component in a system when the
             Performance Expectation                      change in energy of the other component(s) and energy flows in and out of the system are known.
                                                          Chemistry: Emphasis is on explaining the meaning of mathematical expressions used in the model. Focus is on
                                                          basic algebraic expression or computations, systems of two or three components, and thermal energy.
               Clarification Statement                    Physics: Emphasis is on explaining the meaning of mathematical expressions used in the model. Focus is on basic
                                                          algebraic expression or computations; systems of two or three components; and thermal energy, kinetic energy,
                                                          and/or the energies in gravitational, magnetic, or electric fields.
