                            MATH 1.MD.A.1 Order three objects by length; compare the lengths of two
                                 objects indirectly by using a third object.
                                 1.MD.A.2 Express the length of an object as a whole number of
                                 length units, by laying multiple copies of a shorter object (the length
                                 unit) end to end; understand that the length measurement of an
                                 object is the number of same-size length units that span it with no
                                 gaps or overlaps. Limit to contexts where the object being measured
                                 is spanned by a whole number of length units with no gaps or
                                 overlaps.
                                 2.MD.B.5 Use addition and subtraction within 100 to solve word
                                 problems involving lengths that are given in the same units, e.g., by
                                 using drawings (such as drawings of rulers) and equations with a
                                 symbol for the unknown number to represent the problem.
