PS1.C: Nuclear                                                                                                       HS.PS1C.a Nuclear processes, including fusion,
Processes                                                                                                            fission, and radioactive decays of unstable nuclei,
                                                                                                                     involve release or absorption of energy. The total
                                                                                                                     number of neutrons plus protons does not change
                                                                                                                     in any nuclear process.
                                                                                                                     HS.PS1C.b Spontaneous radioactive decays follow
                                                                                                                     a characteristic exponential decay law. Nuclear
                                                                                                                     lifetimes allow radiometric dating to be used to
                                                                                                                     determine the ages of rocks and other materials.
