                                                                                         Grade 7:
                                                                                         MS.PS3A.e The term “heat” as used in
                                                                                         everyday language refers both to thermal
                                                                                         energy (the motion of atoms or molecules
                                                                                         within a substance) and the transfer of that
                                                                                         thermal energy from one object to another. In
                                                                                         science, heat is used only for this second
                                                                                         meaning; it refers to the energy transferred
                                                                                         due to the temperature difference between
                                                                                         two objects.
