EARTH AND HUMAN ACTIVITY
             Performance Expectation                      Ask questions to clarify evidence of the factors that have caused the rise in global temperatures over the past century.
                                                          Examples of factors include human activities (such as fossil fuel combustion, cement production, and agricultural
                                                          activity) and natural processes (such as changes in incoming solar radiation or volcanic activity). Examples of
              Clarification Statement                     evidence can include tables, graphs, and maps of global and regional temperatures, atmospheric levels of gases
                                                          such as carbon dioxide and methane, and the rates of human activities. Emphasis is on the major role that human
                                                          activities play in causing the rise in global temperatures.)
