              Clarification Statement                        the moon’s revolution around Earth explains the cycle of spring/neap tides and the occurrence of eclipses; the
                                                             moon’s elliptical orbit mostly explains the occurrence of total and annular eclipses. Examples of models can be
                                                             physical, graphical, or conceptual.
