                                                                                                                                                          K-ESS2-1
EARTH’S SYSTEMS
             Performance Expectation                    Use and share observations of local weather conditions to describe patterns over time.
                                                        Examples of qualitative observations could include descriptions of the weather (such as sunny, cloudy, rainy, or
                                                        warm); examples of quantitative observations could include numbers of sunny, windy, or rainy days in a month.
              Clarification Statement                   Examples of patterns could include that it is cooler in the morning than in the afternoon or the number of sunny
                                                        days versus cloudy days in different months.
         Science & Engineering Practices                               Disciplinary Core Ideas                                    Crosscutting Concepts
