                                                            Use a model to represent the relationship between the needs of different plants or animals (including humans) and
             Performance Expectation                        the places they live.
                                                            Examples of relationships could include that deer eat buds and leaves and therefore usually live in forested
              Clarification Statement                       areas; grasses need sunlight so they often grow in meadows. Plants, animals, and their surroundings make up a system.
